SIMPLE: prepense
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prepense
<hw>Pre*pense"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>pre</ets> + F. <ets>penser</ets> to think. See
<er>Pansy</er>.]</ety> <def>To weigh or consider beforehand; to
premeditate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser. Sir T.
Elyot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prepense</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prepense
<hw>Pre*pense"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To deliberate
beforehand.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prepense</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Prepense
<hw>Pre*pense"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Pansy</er>, and cf.
<er>Prepense</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>Devised, contrived, or
planned beforehand; preconceived; premeditated; aforethought; -- usually
placed after the word it qualifies; <as>as, malice
<ex>prepense</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This has not arisen from any misrepresentation or error
<qex>prepense</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prepensely</ent>⟦br⟧
